[3] UK (travel alert)
Date: Sat 14 May 2011
Source: The Independent newspaper [edited]


Parents planning to take children to France on holiday should get
them vaccinated against measles because France is in the grip of an
epidemic, the Health Protection Agency says.

France has had 7000 cases of measles so far this year [2011],
according to the HPA. In the UK, there have been 275 laboratory
confirmed cases since the start of the year, compared with 33 in the
same period last year.

[Byline: Jeremy Laurance]

