[6] Bangladesh (Bandarban)
Date: Sat 14 May 2011
Source: bdnews24.com [edited]
http://bdnews24.com/corr/mus/dd/has/nih/mr/2240h


Illnesses caused by measles [virus] infection have killed at least 3
children in the Amtali area of Lama upazila [district] last week.
Doctors on Saturday [14 May 2011] said over 100 Murang children of the
upazila had been suffering due to the infection.

Bandarban civil surgeon Sakhawat Hossain told bdnews24.com that one
child died in the hospital on Friday [13 May 2011], while 2 others
died at their own residences on Tuesday [10 May 2011]. He said they
died due to diarrhoea and pneumonia, caused by measles infection.

Hossain said 17 children were still undergoing treatment at the
health complex. Many are being treated locally by a medical team. One
medical team has been deployed in each upazila.

Acting health and family planning officer of Lama Shafiur Rahman said
measles was spreading in the area due to hot and humid weather and
lack of safe drinking water.

--
