[11] USA (Massachusetts)
Date: Tue 10 May 2011
Source: The Boston Herald, Associated Press report [edited]
http://www.bostonherald.com/business/healthcare/view.bg?articleid=1336971&srvc=business&position=recent


Massachusetts health officials are reporting an increase in the
number of cases of measles, with 5 new cases of the disease confirmed
in the past week. This brings the total for the year to 10 confirmed
cases. Officials say those who contracted the disease range in age
from 16 months to 65 years. They say there is no known connection
between the cases.

The information was contained in an advisory sent out by the state
Department of Public Health to clinicians and health care
professionals across the state. Health officials are urging residents
to check the status of their vaccination history to make sure they are
protected against the disease.

