[12] USA (New York)
Date: Fri 13 May 2011
Source: Newsday.com [edited]
http://www.newsday.com/long-island/nassau/measles-exposure-at-winthrop-hospital-1.2872861?qr=1


People who were at Winthrop-University Hospital in Mineola during a
2-day period last week may have been exposed to measles, the Nassau
County Department of Health warned Thursday [12 May 2011].

The hospital, as well as Nassau and state health officials, confirmed
the case in a traveler from overseas and said visitors to Winthrop
during 2 time periods may have been exposed to the highly contagious
viral infection.

